# Role-based UI rules

Use `src/lib/roles.js` for all role routing and nav selection. Do not hardcode `/student/dashboard` as a fallback for unknown roles.

## Roles
- `student` → prefix `/student`, nav `STUDENT_NAV`
- `startup` → prefix `/startup`, nav `STARTUP_NAV`
- `institution` → prefix `/institution`, nav `INSTUTION_NAV`
- `admin` → prefix `/admin`, nav `ADMIN_NAV`

## Login & redirects
- After login, call `resolvePostLoginPath(role, next)` — never send startup/institution users to `/student/*` paths.
- Login links from startup/institution flows must include `?role=startup` or `?role=institution`.
- Use `loginCopyForRole(role)` and `registerLabelForRole(role)` on auth pages — avoid student-only copy when role is set.

## Dashboard layout
- Use `navForRole(user.role)` for sidebar nav in shared pages (Help, Messages, Notifications).
- Use `profileDisplayName(profile, user)` — supports `full_name`, `name`, `founder_name`, `placement_officer`.
- Use `profileEditPath(role)` for the user menu — all three non-admin roles must have an edit entry.

## Shared components
- Never default shared pages to `STUDENT_NAV` when `user.role` is `institution` or `startup`.
- Messages and Notifications must use `navForRole`, not ternary student/startup only.

## Protected routes
- `ProtectedRoute` redirects wrong-role access via `roleHome(user.role)`.
